from scipy import stats

# Compute Z-scores on scaled data
z_scores = stats.zscore(df_scaled)

# Identify rows with any feature having z-score > 3
outliers = (abs(z_scores) > 3).any(axis=1)

# Remove them
df_scaled_no_outliers = df_scaled[~outliers]

print("Original size:", df_scaled.shape)
print("After outlier removal:", df_scaled_no_outliers.shape)

from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectKBest, f_classif
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE

# Prepare features and target
X = df_scaled.drop(columns=['Dry Eye Disease'])
y = df_scaled['Dry Eye Disease']

# Select top 20 features
selector = SelectKBest(score_func=f_classif, k=20)
X_selected = selector.fit_transform(X, y)
selected_features = X.columns[selector.get_support()]
X_selected_df = pd.DataFrame(X_selected, columns=selected_features)

# Train/test split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X_selected_df, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=42
)

# Apply SMOTE
smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
X_train_res, y_train_res = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)

# Scale features
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_res)
X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)

from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV

param_grid = {
    'C': [0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 1, 10, 100],
    'solver': ['liblinear', 'saga']
}

grid = GridSearchCV(
    LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000),
    param_grid,
    cv=5,
    scoring='accuracy',
    n_jobs=-1
)
grid.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_res)

# Save best model
best_model = grid.best_estimator_

# Prepare features and target
X = df_scaled.drop(columns=['Dry Eye Disease'])

from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectKBest, mutual_info_classif
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score, roc_auc_score, classification_report
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE

#  Step 1: Feature Selection using mutual_info_classif
X = df_scaled.drop(columns=['Dry Eye Disease'])
y = df_scaled['Dry Eye Disease']

selector = SelectKBest(score_func=mutual_info_classif, k=12)
X_selected = selector.fit_transform(X, y)
selected_features = X.columns[selector.get_support()]
print(" Top 12 Selected Features:", selected_features.tolist())

# Step 2: Train/Test Split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X_selected, y, stratify=y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42
)

# Step 3: SMOTE to balance classes
smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
X_train_balanced, y_train_balanced = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)

# Step 4: Train Random Forest (tuned)
rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200, max_depth=8, random_state=42)
rf.fit(X_train_balanced, y_train_balanced)

# Step 5: Predict and evaluate
y_pred = rf.predict(X_test)
y_prob = rf.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

print("\n Model Evaluation:")
print("Accuracy:", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
print("F1 Score:", f1_score(y_test, y_pred))
print("AUC:", roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob))
print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))

from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, AdaBoostClassifier, VotingClassifier

# Define individual models
log_model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000)
rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)
ada = AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)

# Combine models into a soft-voting ensemble
voting = VotingClassifier(
    estimators=[
        ('logreg', log_model),
        ('rf', rf),
        ('ada', ada)
    ],
    voting='soft'  # soft voting uses predicted probabilities
)

# Fit the ensemble model
voting.fit(X_train_balanced, y_train_balanced)

from sklearn.ensemble import StackingClassifier
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, AdaBoostClassifier

# Base models
estimators = [
    ('rf', rf),        # Random Forest (already trained)
    ('ada', ada),      # AdaBoost (already trained)
    ('logreg', log_model)  # Logistic Regression (already trained)
]

# Meta model (can change to another one if needed)
final_estimator = LogisticRegression()

# Build stacking classifier
stack_model = StackingClassifier(
    estimators=estimators,
    final_estimator=final_estimator,
    cv=5,
    n_jobs=-1
)

# Train on balanced data
stack_model.fit(X_train_balanced, y_train_balanced)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score, roc_auc_score

# Dictionary of model predictions and probabilities
model_predictions = {
    "Logistic Regression": (y_pred_logistic, y_prob_logistic),
    "KNN": (y_pred_knn, y_prob_knn),
    "Naive Bayes": (y_pred_nb, y_prob_nb),
    "SVM Linear": (y_pred_svm_linear, y_prob_svm_linear),
    "SVM RBF": (y_pred_svm_rbf, y_prob_svm_rbf),
    "Best SVM (GridSearch)": (y_pred_svm_best, y_prob_svm_best),
    "Decision Tree": (y_pred_dt, y_prob_dt),
    "Random Forest": (y_pred, y_prob),  # Make sure these are Random Forest predictions
    "AdaBoost": (y_pred_ada, y_prob_ada),
    "Gradient Boosting": (y_pred_gb, y_prob_gb),
    "XGBoost": (y_pred_xgb, y_prob_xgb),
    "Bagging": (y_pred_bag, y_prob_bag),
    "Voting Classifier": (y_pred_voting, y_prob_voting),
    "Stacking Classifier": (y_pred_stack, y_prob_stack)
}

# Calculate performance metrics
performance = {
    model: [
        accuracy_score(y_test, preds),
        f1_score(y_test, preds),
        roc_auc_score(y_test, probs)
    ]
    for model, (preds, probs) in model_predictions.items()
}

# Convert to DataFrame
df_performance = pd.DataFrame(performance, index=["Accuracy", "F1 Score", "AUC"]).T

# Sort by accuracy (you can change to 'F1 Score' or 'AUC' if you want)
df_performance = df_performance.sort_values(by="Accuracy", ascending=False)

# Print table
print(df_performance)

# Plot grouped bar chart
df_performance.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(18, 6))
plt.title("Comparison of Model Performance (Accuracy, F1 Score, AUC)")
plt.ylabel("Score")
plt.ylim(0.5, 1.05)
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.grid(axis='y')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
